    "ocr_text": "423
LP March 17, 1908

Speaker of the
House of the New Jersey State Legislature,
Trenton, N.J.

Dear Sir:

I understand that there has recently been introduced
in the New Jersey State Legislature, a bill authorizing an inquiry
into the educational system of the State, as to the establishment
of industrial and technical schools. I would appreciate it very
much if you would kindly send me several copies of this bill.

Thanking you in advance for your courtesy, I am,

Very truly yours,

(Signed)
President
American Federation of Labor

N.B.

Please also send me several copies of the Employers'
Liability Bill, which was introduced in the New Jersey State
Legislature by Mr. Blauvelt.",
    "summary": "Request for copies of two bills from the New Jersey State Legislature: one concerning the establishment of industrial and technical schools, and another concerning employer liability.",
